First, we need to find the sum of the solutions of the quadratic equation $-32x^2 + 84x + 135=0$ using the formula for the sum of the roots of a quadratic equation:
$$
\begin{align}
\text{Sum of the roots} &= -\frac{b}{a} \\
&= -\frac{84}{-32} \\
&= \boxed{\frac{21}{8}}
\end{align}
$$
