To simplify the expression $x(3x^2-2)-5(x^2-2x+7)$, we will distribute $x$ and $-5$ across the terms inside the parentheses, then combine like terms.

\begin{align*}
x(3x^2-2)-5(x^2-2x+7) &= 3x^3-2x-5x^2+10x-35 \\
&= 3x^3-5x^2+8x-35
\end{align*}

So, the simplified form of the expression is $3x^3-5x^2+8x-35$. Thus, the final answer is $\boxed{3x^3-5x^2+8x-35}$.
